{"id":80812,"title":"[Cutaneous leishmaniasis and multidermatomic herpes zoster].","abstract":"Standard treatment of leishmaniasis consists of n-metilglucamine, meglumine antimoniate, which can trigger side effects such as general malaise, renal and hepatic impairment, and cardiac arrhythmias. Infrequently, reactivations of varicella-zoster virus infections have been reported. This paper describes a patient with cutaneous leishmaniasis in treatment with meglumine and herpes zoster multiplex. After ruling out other possible causes of immunosuppression, an acyclovir therapy was initiated. ","date":"2014-02-13","categories":"Parasitic Diseases","split":"test","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24522317","annotations":[{"name":"Herpes zoster","weight":0.892624,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Herpes_zoster"},{"name":"Aciclovir","weight":0.852679,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aciclovir"},{"name":"Malaise","weight":0.830373,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Malaise"},{"name":"Immunosuppression","weight":0.808183,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Immunosuppression"},{"name":"Liver failure","weight":0.801888,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Liver_failure"},{"name":"Virus","weight":0.801843,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Virus"},{"name":"Therapy","weight":0.750676,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Therapy"},{"name":"Cardiac dysrhythmia","weight":0.738087,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cardiac_dysrhythmia"},{"name":"Adverse effect","weight":0.735541,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Adverse_effect"},{"name":"Skin","weight":0.723286,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Skin"},{"name":"Liver","weight":0.71741,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Liver"},{"name":"Infection","weight":0.683991,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Infection"},{"name":"Herpes simplex","weight":0.68346